        <div type="recipe">
        <p> Pickle them red as you do to dry, and when you think them salt enough, boil them very tender; take them up, peel and rub them with Pepper, Cloves and Mace all over; then turn them round into a Pot to bake; lay them in single Pots on their Sides; you must cut off the Root as well as the Skin, and cover them with <objectName ref="#butter">Butter</objectName>; bake them with brown Bread; pour out the Gravy when they come out of the Oven, and let the same <objectName ref="#butter">Butter</objectName> do when cleared; to which, if there be not enough, add more clarified. </p>
            </div>
